latestPosts.caption:
Link For Print Shop in Bio:// The world feels especially chaotic right now. Uncertain, loud, heavy in ways that are hard to put into words. I have felt it deeply in my own heart, and more than ever, I find myself drawn to retreat inward. To quiet spaces. To my studio. To the slow, steady act of creating as a way to find stillness again.

Painting has always been where I land when things feel overwhelming. It is where I soften. Where I breathe. Where I reconnect to what matters most, so that I can show up fully for my family, my kids, and the community around me with a steadier heart. Stillness and beauty feel essential to the human spirit, not as a luxury, but as a lifeline. And right now, sharing that feels more important than ever.

That deep pull toward stillness is why I am pouring so much of my energy into creating new oil painting classes. I want to offer a gentle invitation to unplug, to step away from the relentless noise and screens and headlines, and to use your hands to make something beautiful. There is something profoundly grounding about creating slowly, intentionally, and with care. It brings us back to ourselves.

In that same spirit, I have decided to open my print shop for one week, starting today, and to offer 20 percent off every single fine art print. Walking into a space that holds beautiful artwork has always felt calming to me. It eases the nervous system, softens the edges of the day, and offers a quiet place to rest your eyes and your heart. I hope these pieces can do that for you too.

My hope is that this opening offers you a small breath of fresh air. A pause. A reminder that beauty still exists, and that it is worth protecting and welcoming into our homes and our lives.

Thank you, always, for being here. For supporting this work. And for choosing softness and beauty in a world that so often forgets their power.

With so much gratitude,
Sarah

Life has felt like such a whirlwind lately, and it has been far too long since I have shared anything on here. There have been some truly life changing, heart bursting, wildly exciting things unfolding behind the scenes over here. The kind of changes that make you stop in your tracks and whisper, is this really happening? We are just waiting on a few final pieces to fall into place before I can share the full story, but I promise, it is big, it is beautiful, and it is coming. Until then, just know that I have been completely wrapped up in all of the magic that is quietly unfolding‚Ä¶ including working on THREE brand new oil painting tutorials! Stay tuned my friends!

This painting is my love letter to winter. Fresh snowfall, soft light, that crisp stillness in the air. It captures everything I adore about this season and the way sunlight transforms even the simplest moments into something extraordinary. This piece, along with 13 others, will be available this evening at 6:30 Mountain Time in my final 24 hour Silent Auction of the year. Each painting begins with an opening bid of $500 CAD with worldwide shipping available. Every one of these works is deeply special to me, and I am so excited to share this Holiday Collection with you! If you would like access to the silent auction, be sure to sign up through the link in my bio.  Special thank you to @danielgreenwoodphotography for the inspiration behind this painting!

I am getting so excited to begin sharing my final collection of 2025! This body of work will be released through one of my signature 24 hour online silent auctions this Thursday evening at 6:30 Mountain Time. There will be 13 original paintings in this collection, each with an opening bid of $500 Canadian, and worldwide shipping is available. I cannot wait to share these pieces with you, and I will be revealing little sneak peeks of what I have been quietly working on as we lead up to the launch! You can sign up for exclusive access to the silent auction through the link in my bio. #sarahmckendryfineart #oilpainting #canadianart #pnw #misty #beautifulbc

latestPosts.caption:
Comment ‚Äúlove‚Äù for a link to the full tutorial!

Here are some punny ideas for inside your strawberry Valentine‚Äôs Day card‚Ä¶

Love you berry much

I‚Äôll pick you from the patch every time

Love you bunches

Sweet like strawberry wine

You‚Äôre berry beautiful/handsome 

What else could you write?

Guys I‚Äôve got plans üëÄ

You know my workbooks? Pre-drawn images, video directions, all that good stuff.

Well I‚Äôm working on Watercolor Kits! More pre-drawn images, video directions, AND high quality watercolor paint and paint brush!

Stay tuned for all you‚Äôll need to make some fabulous watercolor masterpieces! ü•≥ü§©ü•∞

Let‚Äôs make watercolor fun!

Sure I could explain the intricate details of how to create a soft edge and tell you to do it on repeat‚Ä¶

Or I could teach you to paint some fluffy clouds and by the end you‚Äôll not only know how to paint a soft edge, but you‚Äôll also have a finished painting you‚Äôre proud of!

Ready? Hit follow and let‚Äôs paint!!

I may be on vacation but I still can‚Äôt help but think of the chaos back in Minnesota.

And yet I‚Äôm still sharing accesible watercolor tutorials, tips, and inspiration. 

I‚Äôve always believed that watercolor is a way to reconnect with our Creator. While my faith is not always explicitly obvious in what I share, I will have you know it impacts my daily decisions to love and honor my neighbors, whoever they are. I believe everyone is made in the image of God and deserves respect and love.

If the world is feeling scary for any reason, may I suggest you pick up a paint brush and try painting something.

You can paint your feelings, or something completely unrelated.

Whatever you do, I hope you know you are loved ü•∞ and you can take a moment to ground yourself in art.

Ready to be proud of what you paint?

Comment ‚Äúyes!‚Äù And I‚Äôll send you the link to the full tutorial!

It‚Äôs one of those paintings that when you‚Äôre done you‚Äôll say ‚ÄúI can‚Äôt believe I made that myself!‚Äù

So what are you waiting for? Happy painting!

‚¨áÔ∏è how to paint this ‚¨áÔ∏è

1. Start by painting a wide oval(ish) area with plain water.

2. Paint trees in a variety of colors, starting above the wet area where the paper is still dry, and ending each tree in that wet oval.

3. Keep the wet area wet by periodically adding water but also remove large puddles with a dry brush or paper towel so it all dries the same speed.

That‚Äôs it!

Let me know how it goes ü§ó

Do all the things you can to stand up for what you think is right.

But don‚Äôt forget to take care of yourself too.

Set down your phone.

Be creative.

Slow down.

Please stay physically and mentally safe, friends ü§ó

Sometimes you just need an easy fun painting to make.

This is one of those! 

I love playing with colors and mixing. Watercolor is perfect for that! 

This would make a super cute card to give a friend or to put on the wall of a playroom.

If you would like more instruction, comment ‚ÄúBird‚Äù and I will send you a link to the full tutorial over on my YouTube channel. 

Happy painting!

Comment ‚Äúlimes‚Äù for the link!

I decided to try a new type of video. This time instead of walking you step-by-step through how to paint it yourself, I‚Äôm thinking out loud while I paint it for me. 

I think you‚Äôll learn a lot about the process of painting by seeing and hearing how I make my own paintings and think through the steps I need to take. 

Go take a watch and let me know if this was helpful and if you want more processed videos like this or if you prefer the step-by-step tutorial tutorials!

What if I said you could have access to 30 fun, short, and beginner-friendly watercolors tutorials to help you start painting more often?

I created the Watercolor Confidence Course to help you build your confidence through quick and achievable paintings. There‚Äôs a variety of subjects covered so you‚Äôll finish it with a wide range of new skills!

The included tutorials are exclusive to this course and they are each less than 10 minutes long. 

The course is structured to help you paint consistently by sending you one week of tutorials at a time. However, you will have access to the tutorials for as long as you want after the fact!

So if you enroll now and start 2026 with a month worth of painting, you could do it again next year!

This month long (with lifetime access) course is only about $2 a day! Comment ‚Äúconfidence‚Äù to get a link to learn more and follow in the footsteps of 100+ beginner watercolor artists just like you!

Ps. Did you spy my studio assistant try to interrupt me? He runs behind me to the window when I ignore himüêï‚Äçü¶∫

There is WHAT on every page?

Comment ME if you can relate and want the link to shop ü§ó

I‚Äôm constantly saving reels and pins and videos from YouTube thinking that one day I will paint them.

But in reality, I use what‚Äôs right in front of me more often. 

It‚Äôs much easier to actually start painting when you have a workbook right in front of you with all the direction and instruction you need in one place. 

What are you waiting for? Comment ME for the direct link to my watercolor workbooks and let‚Äôs start painting!

You can take me out of the classroom but you can‚Äôt take the teacher out of me üòä

After five years of teaching elementary art in public school, I decided to leave to become a full-time artist and teach on my own. 

Now I get to teach everyone, everywhere, whenever, and all the time! 

From here on Instagram, to over on YouTube, and even through online courses, and in person classes, I get to share the joy of watercolor. 

I believe that watercolor is one of the most accessible mediums to explore. If the blank page intimidates you, I have 30 prompts to get your creative juices flowing so that you can start painting.

Comment ‚Äúideas‚Äù to get the PDF!

analytics.vibeDescription: The network surrounding Rustlers UK is heavily anchored in 'British Lad Culture' and 'Foodie' subcultures. There is a dominant cluster of snack reviewers and food aggregators, suggesting an audience constantly seeking new convenience foods. This overlaps significantly with regional UK meme pages (Manchester, Birmingham, London) and sports entertainment (Football, Darts), painting a picture of a young-adult, mass-market UK demographic interested in humour, sports, and fast food. Surprisingly, there are distinct pockets of 'Art/Watercolor' and 'Space/Science' enthusiasts, likely representing the diverse personal interests of the followers beyond their consumption habits.

visualAnalysis.vibeDescription: A dynamic mix of bold graphic design and personal photography, featuring high-contrast black and white elements punctuated by vibrant warm tones. The collection blends professional branding with casual, authentic lifestyle moments.

analytics.vibeDescription: The network surrounding Rustlers UK is heavily anchored in 'British Lad Culture' and 'Foodie' subcultures. There is a dominant cluster of snack reviewers and food aggregators, suggesting an audience constantly seeking new convenience foods. This overlaps significantly with regional UK meme pages (Manchester, Birmingham, London) and sports entertainment (Football, Darts), painting a picture of a young-adult, mass-market UK demographic interested in humour, sports, and fast food. Surprisingly, there are distinct pockets of 'Art/Watercolor' and 'Space/Science' enthusiasts, likely representing the diverse personal interests of the followers beyond their consumption habits.

latestPosts.caption:
Link For Print Shop in Bio:// The world feels especially chaotic right now. Uncertain, loud, heavy in ways that are hard to put into words. I have felt it deeply in my own heart, and more than ever, I find myself drawn to retreat inward. To quiet spaces. To my studio. To the slow, steady act of creating as a way to find stillness again.

Painting has always been where I land when things feel overwhelming. It is where I soften. Where I breathe. Where I reconnect to what matters most, so that I can show up fully for my family, my kids, and the community around me with a steadier heart. Stillness and beauty feel essential to the human spirit, not as a luxury, but as a lifeline. And right now, sharing that feels more important than ever.

That deep pull toward stillness is why I am pouring so much of my energy into creating new oil painting classes. I want to offer a gentle invitation to unplug, to step away from the relentless noise and screens and headlines, and to use your hands to make something beautiful. There is something profoundly grounding about creating slowly, intentionally, and with care. It brings us back to ourselves.

In that same spirit, I have decided to open my print shop for one week, starting today, and to offer 20 percent off every single fine art print. Walking into a space that holds beautiful artwork has always felt calming to me. It eases the nervous system, softens the edges of the day, and offers a quiet place to rest your eyes and your heart. I hope these pieces can do that for you too.

My hope is that this opening offers you a small breath of fresh air. A pause. A reminder that beauty still exists, and that it is worth protecting and welcoming into our homes and our lives.

Thank you, always, for being here. For supporting this work. And for choosing softness and beauty in a world that so often forgets their power.

With so much gratitude,
Sarah

Life has felt like such a whirlwind lately, and it has been far too long since I have shared anything on here. There have been some truly life changing, heart bursting, wildly exciting things unfolding behind the scenes over here. The kind of changes that make you stop in your tracks and whisper, is this really happening? We are just waiting on a few final pieces to fall into place before I can share the full story, but I promise, it is big, it is beautiful, and it is coming. Until then, just know that I have been completely wrapped up in all of the magic that is quietly unfolding‚Ä¶ including working on THREE brand new oil painting tutorials! Stay tuned my friends!

This painting is my love letter to winter. Fresh snowfall, soft light, that crisp stillness in the air. It captures everything I adore about this season and the way sunlight transforms even the simplest moments into something extraordinary. This piece, along with 13 others, will be available this evening at 6:30 Mountain Time in my final 24 hour Silent Auction of the year. Each painting begins with an opening bid of $500 CAD with worldwide shipping available. Every one of these works is deeply special to me, and I am so excited to share this Holiday Collection with you! If you would like access to the silent auction, be sure to sign up through the link in my bio.  Special thank you to @danielgreenwoodphotography for the inspiration behind this painting!

I am getting so excited to begin sharing my final collection of 2025! This body of work will be released through one of my signature 24 hour online silent auctions this Thursday evening at 6:30 Mountain Time. There will be 13 original paintings in this collection, each with an opening bid of $500 Canadian, and worldwide shipping is available. latestPosts.caption:
Comment ‚Äúlove‚Äù for a link to the full tutorial!

Here are some punny ideas for inside your strawberry Valentine‚Äôs Day card‚Ä¶

Love you berry much

I‚Äôll pick you from the patch every time

Love you bunches

Sweet like strawberry wine

You‚Äôre berry beautiful/handsome 

What else could you write?

Guys I‚Äôve got plans üëÄ

You know my workbooks? Pre-drawn images, video directions, all that good stuff.

Well I‚Äôm working on Watercolor Kits! More pre-drawn images, video directions, AND high quality watercolor paint and paint brush!

Stay tuned for all you‚Äôll need to make some fabulous watercolor masterpieces! ü•≥ü§©ü•∞

Let‚Äôs make watercolor fun!

Sure I could explain the intricate details of how to create a soft edge and tell you to do it on repeat‚Ä¶

Or I could teach you to paint some fluffy clouds and by the end you‚Äôll not only know how to paint a soft edge, but you‚Äôll also have a finished painting you‚Äôre proud of!

Ready? Hit follow and let‚Äôs paint!!

I may be on vacation but I still can‚Äôt help but think of the chaos back in Minnesota.

And yet I‚Äôm still sharing accesible watercolor tutorials, tips, and inspiration. 

I‚Äôve always believed that watercolor is a way to reconnect with our Creator. While my faith is not always explicitly obvious in what I share, I will have you know it impacts my daily decisions to love and honor my neighbors, whoever they are. I believe everyone is made in the image of God and deserves respect and love.

If the world is feeling scary for any reason, may I suggest you pick up a paint brush and try painting something.

You can paint your feelings, or something completely unrelated.

Whatever you do, I hope you know you are loved ü•∞ and you can take a moment to ground yourself in art.

Ready to be proud of what you paint?

Comment ‚Äúyes!‚Äù And I‚Äôll send you the link to the full tutorial!

It‚Äôs one of those paintings that when you‚Äôre done you‚Äôll say ‚ÄúI can‚Äôt believe I made that myself!‚Äù

So what are you waiting for? Happy painting!

‚¨áÔ∏è how to paint this ‚¨áÔ∏è

1. Start by painting a wide oval(ish) area with plain water.

2. Paint trees in a variety of colors, starting above the wet area where the paper is still dry, and ending each tree in that wet oval.

3. Keep the wet area wet by periodically adding water but also remove large puddles with a dry brush or paper towel so it all dries the same speed.

That‚Äôs it!

Let me know how it goes ü§ó

Do all the things you can to stand up for what you think is right.

But don‚Äôt forget to take care of yourself too.

Set down your phone.

Be creative.

Slow down.

Please stay physically and mentally safe, friends ü§ó

Sometimes you just need an easy fun painting to make.

This is one of those! 

I love playing with colors and mixing. Watercolor is perfect for that! 

This would make a super cute card to give a friend or to put on the wall of a playroom.

If you would like more instruction, comment ‚ÄúBird‚Äù and I will send you a link to the full tutorial over on my YouTube channel. 

Happy painting!

Comment ‚Äúlimes‚Äù for the link!

I decided to try a new type of video. This time instead of walking you step-by-step through how to paint it yourself, I‚Äôm thinking out loud while I paint it for me. 

I think you‚Äôll learn a lot about the process of painting by seeing and hearing how I make my own paintings and think through the steps I need to take. 

Go take a watch and let me know if this was helpful and if you want more processed videos like this or if you prefer the step-by-step tutorial tutorials!

What if I said you could have access to 30 fun, short, and beginner-friendly watercolors tutorials to help you start painting more often?

I created the Watercolor Confidence Course to help you build your confidence through quick and achievable paintings. There‚Äôs a variety of subjects covered so you‚Äôll finish it with a wide range of new skills!

The included tutorials are exclusive to this course and they are each less than 10 minutes long. 

The course is structured to help you paint consistently by sending you one week of tutorials at a time. However, you will have access to the tutorials for as long as you want after the fact!

So if you enroll now and start 2026 with a month worth of painting, you could do it again next year!

This month long (with lifetime access) course is only about $2 a day! Comment ‚Äúconfidence‚Äù to get a link to learn more and follow in the footsteps of 100+ beginner watercolor artists just like you!

Ps. Did you spy my studio assistant try to interrupt me? He runs behind me to the window when I ignore himüêï‚Äçü¶∫

There is WHAT on every page?

Comment ME if you can relate and want the link to shop ü§ó

I‚Äôm constantly saving reels and pins and videos from YouTube thinking that one day I will paint them.

But in reality, I use what‚Äôs right in front of me more often. 

It‚Äôs much easier to actually start painting when you have a workbook right in front of you with all the direction and instruction you need in one place. 

What are you waiting for? Comment ME for the direct link to my watercolor workbooks and let‚Äôs start painting!

You can take me out of the classroom but you can‚Äôt take the teacher out of me üòä

After five years of teaching elementary art in public school, I decided to leave to become a full-time artist and teach on my own. 

Now I get to teach everyone, everywhere, whenever, and all the time! 

From here on Instagram, to over on YouTube, and even through online courses, and in person classes, I get to share the joy of watercolor. 

I believe that watercolor is one of the most accessible mediums to explore. If the blank page intimidates you, I have 30 prompts to get your creative juices flowing so that you can start painting.

Comment ‚Äúideas‚Äù to get the PDF!
